reviewText: This is such a cute Video !
My 2 year old loves Dora and this is a great DVD.
The granddaughters are really into Dora so they were excited to get a new dvd .  Arrived on a timely basis.
My 2 1/2 yr old daughter loves Dora. Her twin 4 yr old brothers also like it. She wanted this DVD specifically and it's one of her favorites.

My daughters love the videos - they are educational, adventurous, and fun.  There is one point in this video where Dora and Boots need to open a door, and they call a rectangular-shaped key a square.  Since all four sides of the shape were clearly not equal, I found that part a sad reflection on their editing. If you skip over that piece, it's a great dvd!
She loved the video. It made the perfect 1st birthday/Christmas gift.it plays well & she enjoyed it. Will do business again.

What we liked about these and all the other Dora episodes is that it's very interactive. Not only are the characters constantly asking questions of the kids but there's always some kind of mission that needs completion. It usually starts by figuring out a way to get from one place to another with the help of Map. This teaches kids step-by-step directions by repeating it over and over again. Some of the episodes also teach counting, sizes, colors, and problem solving. All of this and some catchy tunes and I can see why my daughter loves Dora.
The movie was not inside the case!!!!
This a good video.  The children like it and it has the ability to teach lessons to little ones.
My  2 years old daughter loves Dora.
great service and product, thank you.
